{
  "__inputs": [],
  "__requires": [
    {
      "type": "grafana",
      "id": "grafana",
      "name": "Grafana",
      "version": "10.0.0"
    },
    {
      "type": "datasource",
      "id": "prometheus",
      "name": "Prometheus",
      "version": "2.x"
    }
  ],
  "annotations": {
    "list": [
      {
        "builtIn": 1,
        "datasource": {"type": "datasource", "uid": "grafana"},
        "enable": true,
        "hide": true,
        "iconColor": "rgba(0, 211, 255, 1)",
        "name": "Annotations & Alerts",
        "type": "dashboard"
      }
    ]
  },
  "description": "Operator-level overview of an OctraVPN node fleet. Every panel pulls from a real NodeMetrics field exposed by /metrics. The slash / preauth / RPC / WireGuard / session-lifecycle panels were filled in by the metrics-plumbing PR; any remaining TODO text panels depend on histograms (audit_flush_seconds, RPC latency) that the hand-rolled exposition format can't carry today.",
  "editable": true,
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "graphTooltip": 1,
  "id": null,
  "links": [],
  "liveNow": false,
  "panels": [
    {
      "type": "row",
      "id": 1,
      "title": "Sessions",
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {"h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0},
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Active sessions (fleet)",
      "description": "octravpn_active_sessions — current entries in the control-plane BoundedMap. Hard cap = CONTROL_SESSIONS_CAP (10000) per node; sessions evict at CONTROL_SESSION_TTL (1h) of idleness.",
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 6, "w": 6, "x": 0, "y": 1},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum(octravpn_active_sessions)",
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "thresholds"},
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {"color": "green", "value": null},
              {"color": "yellow", "value": 5000},
              {"color": "red", "value": 9000}
            ]
          },
          "unit": "short"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {"values": false, "calcs": ["lastNotNull"], "fields": ""},
        "orientation": "auto",
        "textMode": "auto",
        "colorMode": "value",
        "graphMode": "area",
        "justifyMode": "auto"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Session announces /s",
      "description": "rate(octravpn_announces_total) — POST /session calls per second, per node.",
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 6, "w": 9, "x": 6, "y": 1},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_announces_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}}",
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "palette-classic"},
          "custom": {"lineInterpolation": "linear", "fillOpacity": 10, "drawStyle": "line"},
          "unit": "ops"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Session state lookups /s",
      "description": "rate(octravpn_state_lookups_total) — GET /session/:id calls per second. Each is one potential receipt-signing.",
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 6, "w": 9, "x": 15, "y": 1},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_state_lookups_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}}",
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "palette-classic"},
          "custom": {"lineInterpolation": "linear", "fillOpacity": 10},
          "unit": "ops"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "id": 10,
      "title": "Settlement",
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {"h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 7},
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Receipts signed /s",
      "description": "rate(octravpn_receipts_signed_total). Every signed receipt has already had its seq bumped in the persistent receipt journal (P1-8/9), so this is also the rate of durable journal writes.",
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 7, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 8},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_receipts_signed_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}}",
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "palette-classic"},
          "custom": {"lineInterpolation": "linear", "fillOpacity": 10},
          "unit": "ops"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Cumulative bytes served (fleet)",
      "description": "octravpn_bytes_served_total — cumulative bytes routed through the onion-router (in + out). Counter; expect monotonic growth.",
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 7, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 8},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum(rate(octravpn_bytes_served_total[5m])) by (instance)",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}}",
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "palette-classic"},
          "custom": {"lineInterpolation": "linear", "fillOpacity": 10},
          "unit": "Bps"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Session no-shows /s",
      "description": "rate(octravpn_session_no_shows_total[5m]). NOTE: the counter exists but no node-side path increments it yet — settlement-side data (settled vs unsettled) lives on the settlement bot. Flat-zero plot today is expected; bumping starts when the settlement-bot scrape lands.",
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 7, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 15},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_session_no_shows_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}}",
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "palette-classic"},
          "custom": {"lineInterpolation": "linear", "fillOpacity": 10},
          "unit": "ops"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Audit-flusher inline fallback /s (disk-stall alarm)",
      "description": "rate(octravpn_audit_inline_fallback_total[5m]) — count of audit writes that bypassed the batched flusher and took the inline-sync-fsync path because the bounded queue was full. Steady-state zero. Non-zero growth means the flusher cannot keep up with audit-emit rate (disk stall, IO error spam, or an OOM-3-style flood). Operator action: check disk health, journal latency, and whether the node is under malformed-audit-emit DoS. See OOM-3 fix in docs/audit/2026-05-20-load-perf-audit.md.",
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 7, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 15},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_audit_inline_fallback_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}} fallback /s",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "palette-classic"},
          "custom": {"lineInterpolation": "linear", "fillOpacity": 10},
          "unit": "ops",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {"color": "green", "value": null},
              {"color": "red", "value": 0.001}
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "alert": {
        "name": "AuditInlineFallbackNonZero",
        "message": "Audit flusher cannot keep up — disk stalled or under audit-emit flood. Inline-fallback path is active; durability preserved, but throughput is degraded to per-line fsync.",
        "frequency": "30s",
        "conditions": [
          {
            "type": "query",
            "query": {"params": ["A", "5m", "now"]},
            "reducer": {"type": "max", "params": []},
            "evaluator": {"type": "gt", "params": [0]}
          }
        ],
        "for": "30s"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "id": 20,
      "title": "Peer connectivity",
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {"h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 19},
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "WireGuard handshakes /s (success vs fail)",
      "description": "rate(octravpn_wg_handshake_success_total[5m]) is bumped on every `TunnResult::WriteToNetwork` (the typed handshake-reply signal boringtun emits — over-counts keepalives but is the best proxy). `_fail_total` increments on `TunnResult::Err`.",
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 7, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 20},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_wg_handshake_success_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}} success",
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        },
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_wg_handshake_fail_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}} fail",
          "refId": "B",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "palette-classic"},
          "custom": {"lineInterpolation": "linear", "fillOpacity": 10},
          "unit": "ops"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Session opens / closes /s",
      "description": "rate(octravpn_session_opens_total[5m]) is bumped at every accepted POST /session; `_closes_total` increments by N each time the idle sweeper evicts N sessions.",
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 7, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 20},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_session_opens_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}} opens",
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        },
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_session_closes_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}} closes",
          "refId": "B",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "palette-classic"},
          "custom": {"lineInterpolation": "linear", "fillOpacity": 10},
          "unit": "ops"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "id": 30,
      "title": "ACL / Auth",
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {"h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 26},
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Preauth mints & redemptions /s",
      "description": "rate(octravpn_preauth_mints_total[5m]) is bumped at every successful POST /admin/preauth (auth-gated). `_redemptions_total` is bumped by the wire-side redeem path through the MetricsSink trait (octravpn-mesh::headscale_bridge).",
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 6, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 27},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_preauth_mints_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}} mint",
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        },
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_preauth_redemptions_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}} redeem",
          "refId": "B",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "palette-classic"},
          "custom": {"lineInterpolation": "linear", "fillOpacity": 10},
          "unit": "ops"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "Slash events (lifetime)",
      "description": "octravpn_slash_double_sign_total. Any non-zero value is a critical incident — see OctravpnSlashEvent alert.",
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 6, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 27},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "sum(octravpn_slash_double_sign_total)",
          "legendFormat": "slash events",
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "thresholds"},
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {"color": "green", "value": null},
              {"color": "red", "value": 1}
            ]
          },
          "unit": "short"
        }
      },
      "options": {
        "reduceOptions": {"calcs": ["lastNotNull"], "fields": "", "values": false},
        "orientation": "auto",
        "textMode": "value_and_name",
        "colorMode": "value",
        "graphMode": "area",
        "justifyMode": "center"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
      "id": 40,
      "title": "Resource",
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {"h": 1, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 33},
      "panels": []
    },
    {
      "id": 41,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Chain RPC requests & error rate",
      "description": "rate(octravpn_rpc_requests_total[5m]) plotted alongside `rate(rpc_errors_total[5m])/rate(rpc_requests_total[5m])` for the error fraction. The counters are bumped by the hub's validator-health loop; one-shot bond/unbond/claim calls are not yet instrumented.",
      "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"},
      "gridPos": {"h": 6, "w": 12, "x": 0, "y": 34},
      "targets": [
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_rpc_requests_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}} requests/s",
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        },
        {
          "expr": "rate(octravpn_rpc_errors_total[5m]) / rate(octravpn_rpc_requests_total[5m])",
          "legendFormat": "{{instance}} error fraction",
          "refId": "B",
          "datasource": {"type": "prometheus", "uid": "PBFA97CFB590B2093"}
        }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {"mode": "palette-classic"},
          "custom": {"lineInterpolation": "linear", "fillOpacity": 10},
          "unit": "short"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 42,
      "type": "text",
      "title": "TODO — RPC body size & latency histograms",
      "description": "",
      "gridPos": {"h": 6, "w": 12, "x": 12, "y": 34},
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "Per-request *latency* and *body-size* p50/p99 still require histograms; the hand-rolled Prometheus exposition format in `control.rs::metrics` only carries counters and gauges. To plot percentiles, migrate the serializer (or add a side-car histogram serializer) before introducing `prometheus::HistogramVec` in the axum middleware. Note: keep label cardinality bounded — route templates (`/session/:id`) not concrete paths."
      },
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "type": "row",
